  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Paul Maitland International Inc. (PMI or the company) is a BVI registered company with three manufacturing facilities in Vietnam and is one of the largest furniture manufacturers in Southeast Asia with 9,000 employees worldwide, 8,900 of which are based in Vietnam.  The company manufactures high quality European style furniture under the trade names of Theodore Alexander and Atelier De La Madeleine.  

The purpose of the project is to help PMI fund additional working capital which is largely driven by the introduction of a new product line and to help the company maintain its competitive advantage which stems from its superior product design capabilities, well-established customer network, high quality production, and ability to serve customers by providing full furniture packages.</narrative>
  </description>
